  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Top, tail, peel and dice your <strong>carrot[s] </strong>finely</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and dice</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s]</strong>, then peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1689672777079-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1689672777079-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1689672777079-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1689672777079-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1689672777079-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken breast portions</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>ground smoked paprika </strong>and <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up – these are your <strong>smoky chicken breasts</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1689672781073-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1689672781073-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1689672781073-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1689672781073-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1689672781073-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid)  with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>smoky chicken breasts</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until lightly charred</p><p>Transfer the<strong> charred chicken</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 12-14 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!), reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1689672785902-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1689672785902-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1689672785902-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1689672785902-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1689672785902-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat with a little drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion </strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Whilst the onion is softening, slice half your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>green chilli[es]</strong> into rounds and set aside for garnish</p><p>Finely chop the <strong>remaining green chilli</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1689672789051-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1689672789051-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1689672789051-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1689672789051-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1689672789051-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [600ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once the onion has slightly softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and<strong> chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>with your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric </strong>and <strong>curry powder</strong> to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1689672793548-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1689672793548-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1689672793548-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1689672793548-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1689672793548-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>diced carrot</strong> and cook<strong> </strong>for 2-3 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Add the <strong>diced pepper</strong>, <strong>basmati rice </strong>and <strong>bay leaf[ves]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>to the pan with the <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>stock </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1689672797622-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1689672797622-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1689672797622-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1689672797622-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1689672797622-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is cooked, gently stir in your <strong>blanched peas</strong> and cook for 1 min or until they're warmed through – this is your <strong>West African-style spicy rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1689672801713-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1689672801713-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1689672801713-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1689672801713-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1689672801713-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>smoky chicken breasts </strong>over the <strong>West African-style spicy rice</strong>, discard the <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chilli rounds</strong></p><p>Drizzle any <strong>remaining juices </strong>from the chicken over the rice</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
